          Libraries in CClib may be updated on occasion.  Providers
          can announce an impending change by posting a notice to
          att.lang.c++.  It is the responsibility of the user to check
          this newsgroup for change announcements.

          A library that is slated to be updated will remain intact up
          to the last day of the month in which the announcement is
          made, after which time (within the first few days of the
          next month) the new version will update the old.  The source
          for each library will include a release date to help the
          user distinguish between versions.  Users should check
          att.lang.c++ at the end of each month to protect versions
          that they need.  If a large library is changed, users are
          encouraged to voice their opinion to the library provider
          and att.lang.c++ as to the relative worth of the old and new
          versions, to avoid having many copies of large libraries on
          many AT&T machines for a long time.

